1
00:00:14,441 --> 00:00:19,879
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:20,714 --> 00:00:28,621
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,689 --> 00:00:34,059
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,128 --> 00:00:38,189
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:44,336
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,072 --> 00:00:51,978
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:56,872
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:56,951 --> 00:01:03,857
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:03,991 --> 00:01:11,056
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,131 --> 00:01:17,798
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,205 --> 00:01:27,773
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:02:01,559 --> 00:02:03,186
<i>Sand Coffin!</i>

13
00:02:06,998 --> 00:02:08,056
<i>I'll</i> do it.

14
00:02:11,102 --> 00:02:13,798
No! Please back me up.

15
00:02:19,711 --> 00:02:21,406
I got sand in my mouth...

16
00:02:21,913 --> 00:02:23,847
P-Please let me go!

17
00:02:29,487 --> 00:02:31,978
You wouldn't be able to do
anything in your current state...

18
00:02:33,158 --> 00:02:34,147
I'll do it.

19
00:02:34,559 --> 00:02:35,821
Please be careful!

20
00:02:35,994 --> 00:02:37,894
That guy attacks with bones!

21
00:02:44,068 --> 00:02:45,296
Like earlier...

22
00:02:45,370 --> 00:02:48,498
he does things like shoot bones
and extrude bones from inside his body...

23
00:02:49,674 --> 00:02:51,539
He controls bones freely!

24
00:02:52,243 --> 00:02:53,801
Gaara of the Desert...

25
00:02:57,248 --> 00:03:00,012
You use sand,
as the name implies, huh...?

26
00:03:05,089 --> 00:03:10,959
<i>Gaara vs. Kimimaro</i>

27
00:03:17,469 --> 00:03:19,869
<i>Tough defense using sand...</i>

28
00:03:21,339 --> 00:03:24,866
<i>He...isn't a close range combat type...</i>

29
00:03:26,277 --> 00:03:29,041
<i>Getting close would be difficult, huh.</i>

30
00:03:37,689 --> 00:03:38,656
<i>It's coming!</i>

31
00:03:40,258 --> 00:03:41,247
Digital Shrapnel!

32
00:03:57,408 --> 00:03:59,205
<i>There's no waste in his movements...</i>

33
00:03:59,377 --> 00:04:02,175
<i>Sure enough,</i>
<i>he's a considerable Taijutsu user.</i>

34
00:04:04,349 --> 00:04:05,680
<i>Attack and defense are one...</i>

35
00:04:05,984 --> 00:04:08,282
<i>He attacks and defends</i>
<i>with sand, huh?</i>

36
00:04:09,854 --> 00:04:13,153
<i>However, the amount of sand</i>
<i>he can control is probably...</i>

37
00:04:14,125 --> 00:04:16,218
<i>...about the amount of sand</i>
<i>inside the gourd.</i>

38
00:04:17,095 --> 00:04:20,428
Gaara of the Desert...
A dopey nickname.

39
00:04:24,235 --> 00:04:26,760
You can't do anything
if you don't have sand.

40
00:04:28,573 --> 00:04:31,064
Going to the trouble of walking around
carrying heavy sand

41
00:04:31,142 --> 00:04:32,200
is the very proof of that.

42
00:04:37,649 --> 00:04:39,014
Sand Shower...

43
00:04:43,421 --> 00:04:44,752
How trite...

44
00:04:47,792 --> 00:04:50,955
As long as I have sand,
I can do anything.

45
00:04:51,129 --> 00:04:52,460
You're the one who's dopey...

46
00:04:53,264 --> 00:04:57,667
It's easy for me to do things
like create sand with dirt...

47
00:04:58,970 --> 00:04:59,868
<i>I get it...</i>

48
00:05:00,371 --> 00:05:04,273
<i>With his own sand he grinds things</i>
<i>like rocks and minerals in dirt</i>

49
00:05:04,342 --> 00:05:05,639
<i>and makes it into sand.</i>

50
00:05:06,311 --> 00:05:09,178
<i>So he was sending his own sand</i>
<i>beneath the ground</i>

51
00:05:09,247 --> 00:05:11,875
<i>and adding new sand, huh...?</i>

52
00:05:13,117 --> 00:05:14,584
<i>Gaara of the Desert...</i>

53
00:05:15,086 --> 00:05:17,350
<i>His nickname isn't just for display.</i>

54
00:05:17,922 --> 00:05:18,946
<i>Excellent!</i>

55
00:05:23,861 --> 00:05:24,759
You did it!

56
00:05:24,829 --> 00:05:25,796
Not yet.

57
00:05:27,198 --> 00:05:29,462
<i>Sand Burial!</i>

58
00:05:43,481 --> 00:05:46,917
I'm reminded of that man
when I look at that guy.

59
00:05:47,018 --> 00:05:47,643
Huh?

60
00:05:48,019 --> 00:05:50,510
Sasuke Uchiha!

61
00:05:51,255 --> 00:05:53,450
He had the same eyes
as that guy...

62
00:05:54,092 --> 00:05:55,024
The same eyes?

63
00:05:56,427 --> 00:05:59,328
<i>Wanting to verify the value</i>
<i>of one's own existence...</i>

64
00:06:00,031 --> 00:06:01,191
<i>Such eyes...</i>

65
00:06:07,672 --> 00:06:09,435
Sasuke!

66
00:06:48,112 --> 00:06:49,636
Sasuke!

67
00:06:55,553 --> 00:06:56,815
Sasuke.

68
00:06:57,655 --> 00:07:00,852
You're here, aren't you?!
At least answer me!

69
00:07:08,866 --> 00:07:11,801
What's gotten into you?!

70
00:07:56,214 --> 00:07:58,114
<i>I don't hate the darkness...</i>

71
00:08:07,925 --> 00:08:11,725
<i>The darkness is where</i>
<i>I was brought up...</i>

72
00:08:44,028 --> 00:08:48,089
Why am I... in a place like this?

73
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:52,592
Did I do something wrong?

74
00:08:59,744 --> 00:09:01,712
Is there really God...?

75
00:09:02,113 --> 00:09:06,174
If there is, why confine me
in a place like this?

76
00:09:12,223 --> 00:09:13,019
Who's there?

77
00:09:14,025 --> 00:09:17,085
It doesn't matter who I am...
Get out!

78
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:26,201
Kimimaro, the time has come to use you...

79
00:09:26,804 --> 00:09:27,498
Huh?

80
00:09:28,206 --> 00:09:31,767
For our sake,
for the Kaguya Clan...

81
00:09:32,376 --> 00:09:33,809
Fight!

82
00:09:38,282 --> 00:09:40,876
<i>Yes... To fight.</i>

83
00:09:41,452 --> 00:09:42,783
<i>That is...</i>

84
00:09:44,055 --> 00:09:46,888
<i>the only thing I can do now.</i>

85
00:10:11,249 --> 00:10:12,944
N-No way...

86
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,951
That's quite some pressure...

87
00:10:27,665 --> 00:10:30,463
I would've been flattened
just like that

88
00:10:30,534 --> 00:10:33,662
had I not made a membrane
of bone just below the skin.

89
00:10:47,118 --> 00:10:50,349
Bones... That guy's a monster, too.

90
00:10:50,855 --> 00:10:52,652
It's a troublesome body, isn't it?

91
00:10:54,959 --> 00:10:56,517
I underestimated you...

92
00:10:56,794 --> 00:10:59,695
But, I won't be caught by
your sand anymore.

93
00:11:09,774 --> 00:11:12,265
Sand Tsunami!

94
00:11:41,005 --> 00:11:43,838
<i>Wow... It's beyond</i>
<i>the scope of</i>

95
00:11:43,908 --> 00:11:46,035
<i>escaping from the sand</i>
<i>or not getting caught...</i>

96
00:12:00,024 --> 00:12:02,117
<i>To think it would change</i>
<i>the terrain itself...</i>

97
00:12:12,136 --> 00:12:13,967
You... You did it.

98
00:12:14,105 --> 00:12:15,037
Not yet.

99
00:12:18,242 --> 00:12:20,142
Giant Sand Burial!

100
00:12:29,387 --> 00:12:31,378
<i>H-He's so strong...</i>

101
00:12:31,923 --> 00:12:35,051
<i>He's gotten even stronger</i>
<i>than when he fought me.</i>

102
00:12:37,295 --> 00:12:39,490
<i>But...this time for sure...</i>

103
00:12:41,099 --> 00:12:42,532
He's a persistent guy...

104
00:12:42,767 --> 00:12:43,495
Huh?!

105
00:12:48,573 --> 00:12:50,404
<i>I'm still...alive...</i>

106
00:12:51,209 --> 00:12:55,111
<i>Then... There's still significance</i>
<i>for me to live.</i>

107
00:12:59,817 --> 00:13:01,307
From now, we're going
to launch a night attack

108
00:13:01,385 --> 00:13:02,682
on the Hidden Mist Village...

109
00:13:03,121 --> 00:13:05,919
As they are disconcerted
from that incident,

110
00:13:05,990 --> 00:13:09,551
now is the perfect time for us
to make them realize our ferocity!

111
00:13:14,132 --> 00:13:19,468
Make them realize the ferocity
of the Kaguya Clan!

112
00:13:19,604 --> 00:13:21,231
- Yeah!
- Right!

113
00:13:22,406 --> 00:13:25,807
What're you doing, Kimimaro?
Get going!

114
00:13:26,878 --> 00:13:28,175
I don't know what to do...

115
00:13:29,046 --> 00:13:31,071
You don't need to think
deeply about it.

116
00:13:31,582 --> 00:13:33,447
Go down to the Hidden Mist Village

117
00:13:33,518 --> 00:13:35,748
and kill every last person
you encounter!

118
00:13:38,923 --> 00:13:42,723
Just act on your instincts!

119
00:13:50,535 --> 00:13:51,900
Are you of the Hidden Mist Village?

120
00:13:58,042 --> 00:13:59,009
No...

121
00:14:02,079 --> 00:14:04,343
I-I see... Excuse me!

122
00:14:11,088 --> 00:14:11,782
Haku?

123
00:14:11,889 --> 00:14:15,450
Oh... no. It's nothing, Zabuza.

124
00:14:15,927 --> 00:14:18,725
We don't have time to be stopping.
Let's hurry!

125
00:14:19,831 --> 00:14:20,661
Right!

126
00:14:25,102 --> 00:14:26,865
<i>He had the same eyes as I...</i>

127
00:14:27,538 --> 00:14:29,563
<i>Before I met Zabuza...</i>

128
00:14:45,423 --> 00:14:46,617
Hold it!

129
00:14:49,627 --> 00:14:54,291
You're a hasty one, aren't you?
I'm not from this village.

130
00:15:01,672 --> 00:15:05,130
The thing you are after is right there...

131
00:15:05,443 --> 00:15:07,240
Now, go.

132
00:15:12,650 --> 00:15:14,413
<i>It seems to have begun...</i>

133
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,747
<i>The Kaguya Clan...</i>

134
00:15:18,322 --> 00:15:23,817
<i>Fools who can only find</i>
<i>their own path of life by fighting...</i>

135
00:15:24,495 --> 00:15:25,894
<i>It was long ago</i>

136
00:15:25,963 --> 00:15:29,660
<i>when a simple minded group that</i>
<i>just enjoyed slaughtering was acceptable.</i>

137
00:15:30,134 --> 00:15:32,227
<i>With a governed organization</i>
<i>as an opponent,</i>

138
00:15:32,303 --> 00:15:34,362
<i>they just become fools</i>
<i>rushing towards death</i>

139
00:15:34,438 --> 00:15:37,464
<i>if they fight only with power...</i>

140
00:15:41,012 --> 00:15:43,572
Are we the only survivors...?

141
00:15:44,315 --> 00:15:46,977
It seems we're surrounded...

142
00:15:47,151 --> 00:15:49,619
The defense was tighter
than we thought.

143
00:15:50,221 --> 00:15:51,586
We have no choice...

144
00:15:51,656 --> 00:15:52,588
Now it's come to this,

145
00:15:52,657 --> 00:15:55,125
take along with you
every person you can!

146
00:15:56,794 --> 00:15:59,854
We'll have them entertain us
as much as possible!

147
00:16:01,399 --> 00:16:03,094
<i>What do I fight for...?</i>

148
00:16:03,668 --> 00:16:05,260
<i>What am I...?</i>

149
00:16:05,903 --> 00:16:08,997
<i>Without knowing anything,</i>
<i>I just kept on fighting.</i>

150
00:16:10,441 --> 00:16:12,909
The time has come to use you...

151
00:16:14,312 --> 00:16:15,779
<i>I'm needed...</i>

152
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:19,142
<i>That was the only thing</i>
<i>that got my body moving.</i>

153
00:16:19,884 --> 00:16:20,680
<i>And...</i>

154
00:16:22,253 --> 00:16:24,778
<i>I was also able to figure out that...</i>

155
00:16:24,855 --> 00:16:27,323
<i>I couldn't live if I didn't fight.</i>

156
00:16:41,539 --> 00:16:43,097
<i>Dawn broke...</i>

157
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:46,467
<i>And I learned that...</i>

158
00:16:46,544 --> 00:16:49,342
<i>I myself was the only one</i>
<i>to survive.</i>

159
00:16:51,148 --> 00:16:53,173
<i>Again, I'm all alone...</i>

160
00:16:55,419 --> 00:16:59,549
<i>By myself, I just wandered</i>
<i>aimlessly from place to place.</i>

161
00:17:04,729 --> 00:17:05,559
<i>This is...</i>

162
00:17:33,190 --> 00:17:35,351
<i>The flower, from back then...?</i>

163
00:17:38,796 --> 00:17:41,128
Why are you blooming
in a place like this?

164
00:17:43,634 --> 00:17:45,534
Why won't you answer?

165
00:17:48,806 --> 00:17:51,001
You're ignoring me, too, huh?!

166
00:17:52,043 --> 00:17:56,002
There's no way you'd be seen
by someone in a place like this, yet you...!

167
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:57,508
That's enough...

168
00:18:00,384 --> 00:18:04,650
Maybe... there's no significance to living.

169
00:18:06,857 --> 00:18:09,348
But you might be able to
discover something interesting

170
00:18:09,427 --> 00:18:12,260
by continuing to live... right?

171
00:18:13,864 --> 00:18:17,356
Like how you discovered that flower...

172
00:18:19,303 --> 00:18:22,363
Like how I discovered you.

173
00:18:26,744 --> 00:18:28,974
Okay, Let's go...

174
00:18:36,987 --> 00:18:40,388
<i>Back then...</i>
<i>Lord Orochimaru said that, but...</i>

175
00:18:42,259 --> 00:18:45,285
<i>People are born with</i>
<i>some kind of significance.</i>

176
00:18:46,197 --> 00:18:51,260
<i>That's what I think...</i>
<i>some kind of important mission.</i>

177
00:18:53,504 --> 00:18:55,233
<i>The mission for me...</i>

178
00:18:57,108 --> 00:19:01,067
<i>is to protect Lord Orochimaru</i>
<i>and his ambition.</i>

179
00:19:07,318 --> 00:19:08,876
What's... that?!

180
00:19:19,230 --> 00:19:24,463
Come back, Sasuke!
Everyone's worried about you!

181
00:19:28,472 --> 00:19:31,873
Damn it...
It's so dark I can't see anything!

182
00:19:33,144 --> 00:19:35,874
<i>You've got better eyes than me.</i>

183
00:19:38,215 --> 00:19:40,581
<i>Sasuke is in the darkness now...</i>

184
00:19:40,918 --> 00:19:42,317
N-Neji?!

185
00:19:42,887 --> 00:19:44,787
<i>You'll be unable to catch up</i>
<i>with Sasuke</i>

186
00:19:44,855 --> 00:19:46,823
<i>if you stop in a place like this...</i>

187
00:19:47,191 --> 00:19:48,123
Neji

188
00:19:50,961 --> 00:19:56,092
Yeah... You're right!
This isn't the time to stop.

189
00:19:57,034 --> 00:20:01,994
Just wait! I'll take Sasuke
back home no matter what!

190
00:20:08,646 --> 00:20:09,840
Sasuke!

191
00:20:34,004 --> 00:20:35,596
<i>Sand Coffin!</i>

192
00:20:56,961 --> 00:20:58,053
<i>That form...?!</i>

193
00:21:11,976 --> 00:21:14,376
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

194
00:21:14,445 --> 00:21:17,471
<i>And you smiled</i>

195
00:21:17,715 --> 00:21:20,013
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

196
00:21:20,084 --> 00:21:22,814
<i>In my own words</i>

197
00:21:22,887 --> 00:21:28,450
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

198
00:21:28,726 --> 00:21:33,993
<i>Despite my doubts,</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

199
00:21:34,265 --> 00:21:39,669
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

200
00:21:39,871 --> 00:21:45,400
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

201
00:21:46,311 --> 00:21:51,578
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

202
00:21:51,983 --> 00:21:58,650
<i>But you don't feel anything for me, do you?</i>

203
00:21:59,157 --> 00:22:01,853
<i>I feel so sad</i>

204
00:22:01,926 --> 00:22:02,824
<i>But...</i>

205
00:22:02,894 --> 00:22:05,294
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

206
00:22:05,363 --> 00:22:08,332
<i>And you smiled</i>

207
00:22:08,466 --> 00:22:11,060
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

208
00:22:11,135 --> 00:22:14,127
<i>In my own words</i>

209
00:22:14,305 --> 00:22:16,637
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

210
00:22:16,708 --> 00:22:19,836
<i>And you smiled</i>

211
00:22:19,911 --> 00:22:22,379
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

212
00:22:22,447 --> 00:22:25,348
<i>In my own words</i>

213
00:22:25,483 --> 00:22:29,977
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

214
00:22:38,496 --> 00:22:40,828
I'm saved. That's excellent.

215
00:22:40,898 --> 00:22:42,422
To think you could do such a thing!

216
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:45,759
He was persistent,
but this is the end...

217
00:22:46,371 --> 00:22:48,339
He'll never come out again.

218
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:50,601
Brainwashed by Orochimaru...

219
00:22:50,675 --> 00:22:55,135
It's not brainwashing!
That person understands me!

220
00:22:56,481 --> 00:22:58,472
What do you guys know?!

221
00:22:59,183 --> 00:23:02,550
Next episode,
"Vengeful Strike! The Bracken Dance!"
